ten%20undersell%20themselves%20when%20talking%20about%20pay%20during%20the%20interview%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20many%20wrongly%20assume%20that%20being%20unemployed%20means%20they%20can't%20negotiate%20for%20a%20higher%20salary%20than%20what%20they've%20been%20offered.%20If%20you%20have%20that%20mentality%2C%20change%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-company-layoffs-laying-off-workers-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELayoffs%20are%20business%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20personal%20indictments.%20What%20matters%20is%20what%20you%20bring%20to%20the%20table.%20Focus%20on%20the%20here%20and%20now%20and%20what%20you%20can%20do.%20Lead%20with%20your%20skills%20and%20results%2C%20not%20the%20layoff%20story%2C%20not%20woes%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20common%20flub%20is%20to%20start%20off%20discussing%20pay%20from%20a%20weak%20position%20by%20making%20comments%20such%20as%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20budgets%20are%20tight.%26quot%3B%20Don't%20do%20that.%20Budgets%20are%20tight%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20arm%20yourself%20with%20data%20before%20sitting%20in%20the%20hot%20seat.%20Look%20at%20sites%20like%20Glassdoor%20and%20Levels.fyi%C2%A0to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20the%20average%20pay%20for%20the%20role%20you're%20seeking%20in%20the%20geographic%20area%20where%20it's%20located.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you're%20face-to-face%20with%20the%20interviewer%2C%20be%20the%20first%20to%20bring%20up%20compensation.%20You%20will%20be%20in%20a%20stronger%20position%20if%20you're%20the%20one%20leading%20the%20conversation.%20Ask%20for%20the%20pay%20range%20to%20see%20if%20it%20aligns%20with%20the%20research%20you%20did.%20If%20it's%20lower%2C%20say%20what%20you%20believe%20the%20correct%20range%20is%2C%20rather%20than%20sell%20yourself%20short.%20It's%20possible%20the%20interviewer%20will%20offer%20to%20look%20into%20whether%20the%20pay%20can%20be%20adjusted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20just%20focus%20on%20base%20salary.%20Ask%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%20the%20whole%20megillah%20%E2%80%94%20signing%20bonuses%2C%20annual%20bonuses%2C%20and%20paid%20time%20off.%20It's%20about%20going%20deep%20and%20asking%20if%20there's%20a%20professional-development%20budget.%20It's%20also%20making%20sure%20that%20you've%20got%20the%20right%20title%20and%20scope%20for%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20you%20should%20now%20be%20ready%20to%20negotiate.%20Speak%20in%20numbers%2C%20not%20feelings.%20There's%20confidence%20in%20data%2C%20and%20confidence%20plus%20data%20is%20a%20cocktail%20that%20often%20is%20very%20palatable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20want%20to%20say%20is%3A%20%26quot%3BBased%20on%20what%20we%20just%20discussed%20and%20the%20impact%20that%20I%20bring%2C%20I'm%20targeting%20a%20compensation%20package%20of%20X.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20stop%20talking.%20Let%20the%20silence%20do%20the%20work.%20Filling%20the%20gap%20with%20nervous%20chatter%20will%20lead%20you%20to%20undercut%20yourself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20recruiter%20or%20hiring%20manager%20responds%20with%20a%20lower%20number%2C%20don't%20immediately%20fold.%20Instead%2C%20ask%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20you%20tell%20me%20how%20you%20arrived%20at%20that%20number%3F%26quot%3B%20You%20want%20them%20to%20ameliorate%20the%20situation%20by%20using%20their%20own%20data%20and%20their%20own%20words.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20hiring%20managers%20love%20speed.%20They%20think%2C%20'oh%2C%20somebody's%20available!%20There's%20no%20waiting%20period.'%20That%20is%20leverage.%20Point%20out%20in%20the%20interview%20how%20you%20would%20be%20free%20to%20hit%20the%20ground%20running%20quickly%20since%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20give%20a%20current%20employer%20the%20standard%20two%20weeks%20of%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20misperception%20that%20recruiters%20get%20paid%20based%20on%20how%20much%20money%20they%20save%20a%20company%20and%20that%20they%20want%20job%20candidates%20to%20accept%20the%20lowest%20offer%20possible.%20In%20reality%2C%20we%20typically%20get%20bonuses%20if%20we%20hire%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20people%20per%20month.%20For%20example%2C%20at%20Amazon%2C%20I%20had%20to%20hire%20at%20least%20six%20people%20in%20that%20timeframe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20interviewed%20a%20laid-off%20candidate%20for%20a%20sales%20job%20at%20a%20software%20company%20who%20told%20me%20she%20thought%20she%20was%20worth%20%24215%2C000%20in%20annual%20base%20salary.%20I%20said%20shoot%20for%20%24230%2C000%20when%20you%20meet%20with%20the%20hiring%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20candidate%20told%20me%20she%20didn't%20think%20she%20could%20do%20it%2C%20so%20I%20asked%20her%20to%20stand%20up%2C%20put%20her%20hands%20on%20her%20hips%2C%20and%20invoke%20the%20Superman%20pose.%20I%20read%20in%20a%20book%20many%20years%20ago%20that%20doing%20this%20boosts%20confidence%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20works.%20The%20hiring%20manager%20ended%20up%20offering%20the%20candidate%20the%20%24215%2C000%20she%20was%20hoping%20to%20get%2C%20and%20she%20accepted%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoff-pay-negotiation-mistakes-job-interview-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755770761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a4b6e0cfc04e97619ba54f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoff-pay-negotiation-mistakes-job-interview-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I've%20noticed%20that%20laid-off%20people%20often%20undersell%20themselves%20when%20talking%20about%20pay%20during%20the%20interview%20process.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sneedleman%40businessinsider.com%20(Sarah%20E.%20Needleman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoff-pay-negotiation-mistakes-job-interview-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%