e%20students%20and%20companies%20will%20see%20a%20drop-off%20in%20the%20number%20of%20potential%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20long%2C%20industries%20that%20are%20already%20grappling%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-population-decline-worker-shortage-labor-birth-rates-immigration-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworker%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20agriculture%20could%20reach%20a%20point%20of%20crisis.%20A%20report%20by%20the%20labor%20market%20analytics%20firm%20Lightcast%20found%20that%20the%20joint%20forces%20of%20baby%20boomers%20retiring%20and%20shrinking%20demographics%20will%20create%20a%20deficit%20of%206%20million%20workers%20by%202032.%20That%20also%20means%20there%20will%20be%20fewer%20people%20contributing%20to%20Social%20Security%20while%20the%20number%20of%20retirees%20grows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20elected%20leaders%20puzzle%20over%20strategies%20to%20boost%20births%2C%20employers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founders-skipping-college-new-dropping-out-palantir-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigher-education%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20scrambling%20to%20bridge%20the%20gap.%20Nathan%20Grawe%2C%20a%20Carleton%20College%20economics%20professor%20who%20is%20widely%20credited%20for%20coining%20the%20term%20'demographic%20cliff%2C'%20says%20the%20problem%20will%20need%20to%20be%20attacked%20from%20multiple%20angles%20at%20once.%20%26quot%3BIt%20won't%20be%20solved%20by%20one%20silver%20bullet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIncentivizing%20Americans%20to%20have%20more%20kids%20has%20become%20a%20popular%20political%20talking%20point%2C%20particularly%20on%20the%20right.%20As%20part%20of%20Donald%20Trump's%20%26quot%3BOne%20Big%20Beautiful%20Bill%2C%26quot%3B%20parents%20will%20now%20receive%20a%20%241%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-account-maga-kids-big-beautiful-bill-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestment%20account%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20every%20new%20baby%20they%20have%20between%202024%20and%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPopulation%20decline%20isn't%20a%20uniquely%20American%20problem.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%20Department%20of%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Affairs%20(UNDESCA)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoming-reign-only-child-americans-fewer-babies-siblings-costs-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efertility%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20below%202%20births%20per%20woman%20are%20%26quot%3Bbecoming%20the%20global%20norm%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20that%20societies%20around%20the%20world%20are%20falling%20short%20of%20the%20required%202.1%20births%20per%20woman%20to%20replace%20the%20population.%20The%20trend%20is%20especially%20pronounced%20in%20high-income%20countries%20where%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20access%20to%20birth%20control%2C%20higher%20education%2C%20and%20professional%20opportunities%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20linked%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-fertility-rate-record-low-delayed-childbirth-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelayed%20childbirth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20generally%20leads%20to%20fewer%20total%20kids.%20But%20women%20in%20many%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20are%20%3Cem%3Ealso%3C%2Fem%3E%20having%20smaller%20families%2C%20even%20in%20places%20where%20marriage%20is%20nearly%20universal%20and%20childbirth%20%3Cem%3Eisn't%3C%2Fem%3E%20delayed%2C%20such%20as%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20single%2C%20clear-cut%20cause%2C%20the%20birth-rate%20decline%20is%20a%20problem%20without%20simple%20solutions.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20believe%20there%20are%20any%20policy%20levers%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%2C%20that%20we%20know%20of%20%E2%80%94%20that%20can%20make%20a%20big%20difference%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Wafa%20Orman%2C%20a%20labor%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eeconomist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alabama%20in%20Huntsville.%20Social%20incentives%20like%20baby%20bonuses%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkers-dont-take-all-parental-leave-because-of-corporate-bias-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eparental%20leave%20help%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Orman%20says%2C%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20flip%20the%20downward%20trajectory%20of%20new%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20the%20country's%20nearly%204%2C000%20degree-granting%20colleges%20and%20universities%20%E2%80%94%20the%20institutions%20most%20immediately%20affected%20by%20the%20demographic%20dropoff%20%E2%80%94%20to%20come%20up%20with%20their%20own%20strategies%20for%20survival.%20For%20some%2C%20the%20challenge%20will%20be%20insurmountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParts%20of%20the%20US%20are%20already%20feeling%20the%20pain.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-states-people-are-leaving-for-cheaper-life-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eout-migrations%20and%20lower%20fertility%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20northeast%20quadrant%20of%20the%20country%20has%20been%20in%20this%20sort%20of%20decline%20for%20a%20while%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grawe.%20Eleven%20of%20the%2031%20degree-granting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fis-college-worth-it%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolleges%20and%20universities%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20shut%20down%20in%202024%20were%20in%20the%20northeast%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20data%20analyzed%20by%20the%20State%20Higher%20Education%20Executive%20Officers%20Association%20released%20by%20The%20Hechinger%20Report.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Philadelphia%20predicts%20that%20as%20many%20as%2080%20more%20schools%20could%20close%20by%202029.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20school%20shuts%20down%2C%20it%20derails%20its%20students'%20lives.%20One%20recent%20study%20found%20that%20less%20than%20half%20of%20students%20(47%25)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-enrollment-crisis-what-is-causing-it-fafsa-student-debt-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edisplaced%20by%20college%20closures%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20on%20to%20re-enroll%20in%20another%20postsecondary%20institution.%20Of%20those%20that%20did%20re-enroll%2C%20less%20than%2037%25%20stuck%20it%20out%20long%20enough%20to%20earn%20a%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20schools%20manage%20to%20survive%2C%20the%20demographic%20cliff%20may%20leave%20them%20ill-equipped%20to%20serve%20all%20students.%20%26quot%3BSome%20smaller%20rural%20campuses%20are%20already%20seeing%20really%20diminished%20program%20offerings%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Betheny%20Gross%2C%20research%20director%20at%20an%20EdTech%20nonprofit%20run%20by%20Western%20Governors%20University.%20That%20means%20already%20underserved%20communities%20end%20up%20with%20even%20fewer%20postsecondary%20options%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20members%20of%20those%20communities%20a%20lot%20less%20likely%20to%20pursue%20higher%20education%2C%20and%20which%20in%20turn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-job-market-rejection-offer-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ediminishes%20job%20prospects%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Georgetown%20University%20Center%20on%20Education%20and%20the%20Workforce%20projects%20that%20by%202031%2C%2072%25%20of%20US%20jobs%20will%20require%20some%20form%20of%20postsecondary%20education%20or%20training%2C%20up%20from%2068%25%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20small-town%20America%2C%20college%20closures%20can%20mean%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20vital%20economic%20lifeline.%20In%20an%20instant%2C%20employers%20lose%20precious%20talent-recruitment%20pipelines%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-elite-mbas-ditching-corporate-america-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elocal%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20lose%20customers%2C%20and%20critical%20public%20services%20are%20wrung%20dry.%20The%20Chronicle%20of%20Higher%20Education%20reported%20that%20when%20Wells%20College%20shut%20its%20doors%20to%20its%20350%20students%20last%20spring%2C%20the%20upstate%20New%20York%20village%20of%20Aurora%20%E2%80%94%20home%20to%20just%20255%20non-student%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20was%20suddenly%20left%20without%20a%20quarter%20of%20its%20volunteer%20firefighters%20and%20a%20%24200%2C000%20tab%20to%20continue%20running%20its%20water-treatment%20plant%2C%20which%20the%20college%20had%20been%20operating%20for%20more%20than%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20students%20and%20rural%20communities%20pay%20a%20particularly%20steep%20toll%2C%20the%20economic%20aftershocks%20are%20significant%20across%20the%20board.%20According%20to%20a%202024%20IMPLAN%20analysis%2C%20each%20college%20closure%20leads%20to%20an%20average%20loss%20of%20265%20jobs%2C%20%2414%20million%20in%20labor%20income%2C%20%2421%20million%20in%20GDP%2C%20and%20%2432%20million%20in%20overall%20economic%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrawe%20sums%20it%20up%20plainly%3A%20%26quot%3BSome%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20are%20going%20to%20face%20some%20really%20stiff%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20academia%2C%20the%20demographic%20cliff%20will%20strain%20the%20entire%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20new%20report%2C%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20(CBO)%20projects%20that%20by%202033%2C%20deaths%20will%20begin%20to%20outpace%20births%2C%20culminating%20in%20a%20smaller%20and%20older-skewing%20population.%20This%20pattern%20of%20demographic%20shrinkage%20leads%20to%20a%20shrunken%20labor%20force%2C%20which%20means%20less%20economic%20growth%20over%20time.%20Japan's%20postwar%20trajectory%20gives%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-fertility-crisis-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprime%2C%20and%20ominous%2C%20example%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20how%20it%20might%20play%20out%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201950s%2C%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Shigeru%20Yoshida%20prioritized%20rebuilding%20the%20nation's%20economy%20by%20encouraging%20corporations%20to%20offer%20lifelong%20job%20security%20in%20exchange%20for%20worker%20loyalty.%20This%20strategy%20helped%20Japan%20grow%20into%20the%20world's%20third-largest%20economy%2C%20but%20it%20came%20at%20a%20cost%3A%20fertility%20rates%20dropped%20from%202.75%20children%20per%20woman%20in%20the%20early%201950s%20to%202.08%20by%201960.%20It%20has%20since%20dwindled%20to%20a%20historic%20low%20of%201.15%20last%20year.%20The%20shift%20piled%20new%20pressures%20onto%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokyo-introducing-four-day-workweek-aims-boost-fertility-babies-japan-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ealready%20overtaxed%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20driving%20a%20more%20than%20trillion-dollar%2C%20or%2020%25%2C%20drop%20in%20the%20country's%20nominal%20GDP%20since%202021.%20Last%20year%2C%20Japan%20lost%20its%20slot%20in%20the%20world's%20top%20three%20economies%2C%20slipping%20to%20fourth%20place%20behind%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20some%20studies%20that%20show%20that%20the%20difference%20in%20economic%20growth%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Japan%20can%20be%20entirely%20attributed%20to%20demographics%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Orman.%20%26quot%3BJapan's%20growing%20more%20slowly%20only%20because%20they%20have%20fewer%20people%2C%20and%20especially%20fewer%20young%20people.%20So%20if%20our%20population%20starts%20to%20shrink%2C%20we%20should%20expect%20to%20see%20the%20same%20thing%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20America's%20demographic%20cliff%20were%20happening%20in%20isolation%2C%20it%20would%20present%20serious%20questions%20about%20the%20nation's%20ability%20to%20maintain%20its%20position%20among%20the%20world's%20major%20economic%20powers.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpopulation-decline-birth-rates-demographics-workplace-hours-productivity-musk-grantham-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epopulation%20decline%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20affecting%20a%20majority%20of%20countries%20around%20the%20world.%20As%20of%202024%2C%20the%20US%20birthrate%20remained%20%3Cem%3Ehigher%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethan%20in%20nearly%20all%20of%20Europe%2C%20the%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20China%2C%20according%20to%20UNDESCA's%20report.%20The%20situation%20presents%20an%20interesting%20thought%20experiment%3A%20If%20the%20population%20plunge%20isn't%20hampering%20the%20US's%20relative%20edge%20in%20the%20global%20market%2C%20is%20slower%20growth%20really%20such%20a%20big%20deal%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrman%20proposes%20a%20longer%20view.%20%26quot%3BMost%20innovation%20comes%20from%20young%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BYoung%20people%20are%20usually%20the%20ones%20that%20are%20more%20creative%2C%20have%20new%20ideas%2C%20and%20see%20things%20in%20a%20different%20way.%20Once%20you%20get%20older%2C%20you%20have%20the%20wisdom%20that%20comes%20with%20age%2C%20but%20you%20are%20less%20creative%20than%20you%20were%20in%20your%20youth.%26quot%3B%20An%20aging%20population%20can%20be%20a%20detriment%20to%20innovation%20and%20progress%2C%20which%20is%20a%20potential%20detriment%20to%20societies%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20happens%20now%3F%20First%2C%20the%20bad%20news%3A%20A%20complete%20reproductive%20rebound%20is%20probably%20off%20the%20table.%20There%20is%20no%20precedent%20for%20pronatal%20policy%20measures%20raising%20birth%20rates%20enough%20to%20get%20population%20counts%20back%20on%20track%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20before%202033.%20According%20to%20the%20CBO's%20report%2C%20the%20only%20surefire%20way%20to%20do%20%3Cem%3Ethat%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-population-decline-worker-shortage-labor-birth-rates-immigration-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpanding%20legal%20pathways%20for%20immigration%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20a%20solution%20rife%20with%20political%20friction.%20Colleges%2C%20companies%2C%20and%20communities%20will%20have%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20hands%20they've%20been%20dealt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20some%20early%20strategies%20to%20adapt%20have%20already%20shown%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenny%20Petty%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20marketing%20and%20communications%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Montana%2C%20says%20that%20the%20school%20saw%20a%2040%25%20decline%20in%20enrollment%20between%202011%20and%202019.%20It%20has%20since%20doubled%20down%20on%20targeting%20non-traditional%20student%20populations%20through%20community-college%20licensing%20programs%20and%20workforce-development%20training%20partnerships%20with%20regional%20employers.%20The%20university%20has%20also%20focused%20on%20improving%20student%20retention%2C%20with%20admissions%20counselors%20shifting%20away%20from%20recruitment%20to%20prioritize%20meeting%20one-on-one%20with%20new%20students.%20Those%20efforts%20have%20paid%20off%3A%20Petty%20says%20that%20the%20university%20has%20seen%20eight%20consecutive%20semesters%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-prefers-trade-school-tech-training-college-degree-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eenrollment%20growth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20retention%20is%20up%20to%2074.8%25%20%E2%80%94%20well%20above%20the%20national%20average%20of%2068.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20University%20of%20Montana's%20multi-pronged%20approach%20reflects%20the%20kind%20of%20strategy%20that%20several%20higher-ed%20experts%20say%20will%20be%20necessary%20for%20colleges%20and%20universities'%20survival%20through%20the%20demographic%20shake-ups%20ahead.%20Student%20retention%20will%20be%20an%20increasingly%20critical%20piece%20of%20that%20puzzle.%20Employers%20and%20communities%20will%20similarly%20need%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20fewer%20workers%20and%20residents%2C%20whether%20by%20leveraging%20new%20technologies%20or%20finding%20creative%20solutions%20for%20developing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyoung%20people's%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20economic%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20that%20we'll%20see%20some%20real%20attention%20to%20student%20success%2C%20and%20there%20are%20institutions%20that%20have%20already%20gotten%20ahead%20of%20the%20demographic%20contraction%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grawe%2C%20the%20Carlton%20College%20economist.%20%26quot%3BA%2015%25%20decline%20in%20enrollments%20is%20very%20challenging%20for%20many%20tuition-dependent%20institutions%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20happening%20all%20at%20once.%20It's%20happening%20bit%20by%20bit%2C%20year%20after%20year.%20So%20that's%20a%20challenge%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20workable%20challenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-great-people-shortage-colleges-employers-birth-rate-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755764223000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a5ed3fa17a8c5b40532937%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-economy-great-people-shortage-colleges-employers-birth-rate-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20US%20birt