20a%20moment%20when%20many%20travelers%20are%20feeling%20extra%20price%20sensitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELas%20Vegas%20has%20relatively%20recently%20developed%20a%20reputation%20for%20being%20expensive%20and%20for%20nickel-and-diming%20people%20at%20every%20opportunity.%20The%20costs%20of%20plane%20tickets%2C%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20food%2C%20drinks%2C%20and%20even%20parking%20have%20skyrocketed.%20The%20nature%20of%20the%20city%20has%20changed%2C%20too.%20Instead%20of%20existing%20as%20America's%20slightly%20seedy%20city%20of%20vice%2C%20Vegas%20has%20gotten%20a%20sort%20of%20glow-up%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20broaden%20its%20appeal.%20The%20upside%3A%20A%20broader%20audience%20might%20be%20up%20for%20a%20trip%20to%20Vegas%20than%20in%20the%20past.%20The%20downside%3A%20Vegas%20now%20resembles%20so%20many%20other%20destinations%20that%20it%20loses%20out%20to%20similarly%20priced%20(or%20even%20cheaper)%20competitors%2C%20especially%20if%20visitors%20aren't%20having%20a%20bang-up%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20starting%20to%20change%20the%20mentality%20of%20the%20visitor%20where%20they're%20thinking%2C%20'Well%2C%20I%20could%20go%20to%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20but%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20pain%20in%20my%20neck%2C%20or%20I%20could%20go%20to%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C'%26quot%3B%20says%20Michael%20Schoenberger%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20hospitality%20management%20at%20the%20College%20of%20Southern%20Nevada.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20cumulative%20effect%20that's%20just%20now%20starting%20to%20show%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat's%20wrong%20in%20Las%20Vegas%26quot%3B%20conversation%20is%20peaking%20right%20now%2C%20things%20have%20been%20shaky%20for%20a%20while%2C%20says%20Amanda%20Berlarmino%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20hospitality%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nevada%2C%20Las%20Vegas.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%20we've%20struggled%20with%20visitation%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsian%20tourism%20has%20not%20recovered%2C%20she%20says%2C%20and%20this%20year%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20decline%20in%20other%20international%20visitors%2C%20including%2C%20importantly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanadians-us-travel-boycott-decline-months-straight-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanadian%20tourism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-canada-economy-tariffs-trade-war-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20antagonism%3C%2Fa%3E%20towards%20America's%20neighbors%20to%20the%20north.%20International%20visitors%20tend%20to%20do%20longer%20stints%20than%20domestic%20visitors%2C%20who%20might%20just%20pop%20down%20for%20a%20weekend%2C%20which%20makes%20their%20pullback%20cut%20a%20little%20deeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20domestic%20picture%20isn't%20especially%20pretty%2C%20either.%20Worries%20about%20the%20economy%20may%20be%20keeping%20Americans%20at%20home.%20A%20disproportionate%20amount%20of%20Las%20Vegas%20visitors%20tend%20to%20come%20from%20California%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reviewjournal.com%2Fbusiness%2Fcasinos-gaming%2Fdespite-strong-june-nevada-gaming-win-numbers-fail-to-break-record-3407733%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumber%20of%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20crossing%20the%20California-Nevada%20border%20on%20Interstate%2015%20declined%20by%204.3%25%20in%20June%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20month%20last%20year.%20Berlarmino%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-damage-photos-landmarks-before-and-after-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echalks%20much%20of%20it%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20fires%20that%20hit%20Southern%20California%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20Schoenberger%20notes%20that%20disruptions%20from%20highway%20construction%20have%20been%20a%20problem%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20Hill%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20LVCVA%2C%20says%20while%20these%20issues%20are%20not%20ideal%2C%20Las%20Vegas%20has%20seen%20worse%20in%20the%20recent%20past.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20not%20the%20crisis%20situation%20like%20we've%20seen%20through%20Covid%20or%20the%20extended%20downturn%20through%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20some%20of%20these%20more%20acute%20issues%2C%20one%20major%20complication%20that's%20gradually%20been%20growing%20may%20finally%20be%20reaching%20an%20inflection%20point%3A%20pricing.%20To%20put%20it%20plainly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-couple-spent-4k-las-vegas-trip-tips-save-money-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELas%20Vegas%20is%20hella%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20longtime%20proposition%20of%20Las%20Vegas%20was%20that%20it%20was%20relatively%20cheap%20to%20get%20there%20and%20stay%20there%2C%20because%20once%20people%20got%20there%2C%20the%20amount%20they%20spent%20on%20gambling%20at%20the%20casinos%20and%20resorts%20more%20than%20made%20up%20for%20it.%20But%20that's%20no%20longer%20the%20case.%20Flights%20to%20the%20city%20may%20still%20be%20slightly%20less%20expensive%20than%20some%20destinations%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20that%20far%20from%20trips%20to%20New%20Orleans%2C%20Miami%2C%20or%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20hotels%2C%20though%20prices%20can%20vary%20widely.%20The%20typical%20clientele%20has%20also%20shifted.%20While%20Las%20Vegas'%20traditional%20market%20was%20people%20over%2060%20who%20tended%20to%20be%20value-conscious%2C%20now%20more%20people%20are%20coming%20in%20their%20prime%20earning%20years%20and%20demanding%20more%20premium%20services%20and%20experiences.%20Resort%20economics%20have%20changed%2C%20too.%20Gambling%20is%20no%20longer%20so%20important%20as%20a%20revenue%20driver%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20hotel%20rooms%2C%20food%20and%20beverage%2C%20and%20events.%20Combine%20all%20of%20that%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-inflation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einflation%20and%20consumer%20wallets%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20squeezed%2C%20and%20you%20can%20see%20why%20some%20visitors%20may%20shorten%20trips%20or%20just%20scrap%20them%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20a%20more%20expensive%20market%20now%20than%20we've%20ever%20been%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Berlarmino%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Las%20Vegas%20casinos%20and%20hotels%20started%20charging%20for%20parking%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%2C%20and%20they're%20piling%20on%20resort%20fees%2C%20too.%20My%20recent%20four-night%20stay%20at%20the%20Cosmopolitan%20Hotel%20included%20%24249.44%20in%20resort%20fees%20and%20associated%20taxes.%20While%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20do%20Las%20Vegas%20that%20aren't%20so%20costly%20%E2%80%94%20staying%20in%20budget%20or%20value%20hotels%20away%20from%20the%20Strip%2C%20buying%20food%20and%20alcohol%20at%20a%20store%2C%20or%20abstaining%20from%20drinking%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20little%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-stop-buying-las-vegas-from-local-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadd-on%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20make%20people%20feel%20like%20they're%20being%20ripped%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20starting%20right%20before%20the%20pandemic%20and%20then%20continuing%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20we've%20introduced%20a%20lot%20of%20pain%20points%20to%20the%20visitors%20that%20historically%20were%20not%20present%2C%26quot%3B%20Schoenberger%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20we%20charge%20people%20to%20drink%20what%20drinks%20cost%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20I%20have%20no%20idea.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHill%20says%20that%20the%20narrative%20around%20the%20cost%20of%20Vegas%20is%20%26quot%3Boverblown%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20says%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Ball%20kinds%20of%20ways%26quot%3B%20to%20achieve%20a%20budget-friendly%20experience.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20150%2C000%20rooms%20and%20they%2C%20right%20this%20minute%2C%20run%20from%20%249%20probably%20to%20%24600%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20slowdown%20in%20visitors%20has%20led%20some%20hotels%20to%20cut%20their%20prices%2C%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsports-betting-odds-gambling-lines-memecoins-prediction-markets-polymarket-stocks-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGambling%20being%20more%20widely%20available%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20the%20US%20is%20both%20a%20blessing%20and%20a%20curse%20for%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20which%20used%20to%20be%20one%20of%20two%20major%20places%20in%20the%20states%2C%20along%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freview-ocean-casino-resort-in-atlantic-city-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAtlantic%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20you%20could%20legally%20bet.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20people%20who%20have%20the%20gambling%20itch%20can%20probably%20find%20a%20place%20to%20scratch%20it%20within%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20from%20their%20homes.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20proliferation%20of%20gambling%20may%20also%20mean%20more%20people%20get%20the%20itch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Grove%2C%20a%20sports-gambling-industry%20investor%20at%20Acies%20Investments%2C%20tells%20me%20the%20growth%20of%20sports%20betting%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20but%20a%20net%20positive%20for%20Vegas.%26quot%3B%20It's%20given%20people%20a%20taste%20of%20betting%2C%20and%20if%20they%20like%20it%2C%20it%20might%20inspire%20them%20to%20go%20to%20the%20biggest%20place%20in%20America%20there%20is%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrove%20compared%20it%20to%20the%20poker%20boom%20of%20the%20early%202000s.%20%26quot%3BOnline%20poker%20got%20really%20popular%2C%20and%20you%20ask%20the%20question%3A%20Did%20that%20do%20anything%20to%20dissuade%20people%20from%20coming%20to%20Vegas%20to%20play%20poker%3F%20And%20the%20answer%20is%20no%2C%26quot%3B%20Grove%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20summer%20is%20a%20slow%20time%20for%20sports%20gambling.%20If%20people%20were%20sitting%20home%20on%20their%20couches%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-obsession-with-betting-sports-investing-elections-athletes-banned-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esports%20betting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20instead%20of%20going%20to%20Vegas%2C%20they'd%20be%20doing%20so%20during%20the%20NFL%20season%20and%20March%20Madness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Vegas%20developments%20have%20been%20a%20mixed%20bag.%20Formula%201%2C%20back%20in%20Vegas%20since%202023%2C%20is%20an%20attraction%2C%20but%20preparing%20for%20it%20has%20caused%20transit%20disruptions%2C%20Schoenberger%20says.%20In%20the%20company's%20second-quarter%20earnings%20call%2C%20MGM%20Resorts%20CEO%20Bill%20Hornbuckle%20said%20that%20Las%20Vegas%20remains%20%26quot%3Bfundamentally%20solid%26quot%3B%20and%20blamed%20the%20company's%209%25%20drop%20in%20earnings%20from%20its%20Strip%20resorts%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Buniquely%20disruptive%20remodel%26quot%3B%20at%20its%20MGM%20Grand%20and%20slow%20mid-week%20bookings%20at%20two%20of%20its%20value%20operations.%20Caesars%20said%20in%20its%20second-quarter%20earnings%20that%20it%20had%20seen%20decent%20gaming%20results%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20during%20the%20period%2C%20even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20weaker%20demand%20for%20its%20hospitality%20offerings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20top%20third-ish%20of%20the%20market%20is%20still%20doing%20exceptionally%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Hill%2C%20of%20the%20Convention%20and%20Visitors%20Authority%2C%20says.%20It's%20when%20you%20get%20into%20the%20middle%20third%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20becomes%20more%20acute%2C%20the%20more%20budget-conscious%20the%20visitor%20needs%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tempting%20to%20ascribe%20to%20Las%20Vegas'%20slowdown%20some%20greater%20meaning.%20Maybe%20it's%20just%20a%20temporary%20blip%2C%20but%20what%20if%20it's%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweird-recession-indicators%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecession%20indicator%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Or%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20times%20and%20proof%20that%20Las%20Vegas%20is%20over%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeclaring%20that%20the%20slow%20summer%20is%20the%20end%20of%20Sin%20City%20as%20we%20know%20it%20would%20be%20a%20bit%20premature.%20The%20same%20goes%20for%20calling%20it%20a%20surefire%20sign%20of%20a%20recession.%20But%20it%20does%20seem%20like%20Vegas%20is%20in%20a%20sort%20of%20weird%20limbo%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20only%20temporary.%20It's%20a%20place%20that%20feels%20stuck%20in%20time%20%E2%80%94%20besides%20some%20of%20the%20outfits%20and%20what's%20on%20the%20TV%2C%20you%20might%20not%20know%20if%20you're%20in%20a%20casino%20in%202010%20or%202025.%20After%20all%2C%20DJ%20Pauly%20D%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjersey-shore-cast-where-are-they-now-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJersey%20Shore%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20fame%20is%20playing.%20Where%20it%20is%20getting%20more%20modern%2C%20like%20the%20additions%20of%20the%20Sphere%20and%20the%20NFL's%20Raiders%2C%20it's%20still%20figuring%20out%20the%20logistics.%20It's%20responding%20to%20consumer%20demand%20for%20a%20higher-end%20experience%2C%20but%20still%20faces%20with%20consumers%20who%20may%20not%20be%20prepared%20to%20pay%20such%20high-end%20prices.%20If%20a%20trip%20to%20Vegas%20is%20going%20to%20run%20you%20the%20same%20as%20a%20vacation%20to%20New%20York%2C%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Miami%2C%20or%20even%20Mexico%2C%20you%20might%20think%20twice%20about%20how%20much%20of%20a%20premium%20you%20actually%20put%20on%20the%20Sin%20City%20experience%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20main%20differentiator%20is%20that%20in%20Vegas%2C%20you're%20surrounded%20by%20tables%20and%20machines%20designed%20to%20suck%20money%20out%20of%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20clear%2C%20Las%20Vegas%20is%20lovely.%20Gambling%20is%20fun%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it%20is%20done%20responsibly.%20The%20shows%20are%20great%2C%20the%20hotels%20are%20comfy.%20Its%20nightlife%20offers%20a%20good%20amount%20of%20(responsible)%20debauchery%2C%20and%20its%20daylife%20is%20fairly%20family-friendly.%20When%20it's%20not%20sweltering%20hot%20out%2C%20the%20outdoor%20stuff%20is%20really%20great%2C%20too.%20Despite%20the%20videos%2C%20pictures%2C%20and%20memes%20floating%20around%20online%2C%20it%20was%20far%20from%20empty.%20(Also%2C%20anywhere%20could%20be%20painted%20as%20bare%20if%20you%20go%20at%20the%20right%20time%20of%20day.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20might%20just%20be%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20slight%20pivot%20moment%20%E2%80%94%20not%20that%20it's%20changing%20its%20identity%2C%20but%20it's%20finding%20an%20identity%20in%20a%20culture%20and%20economy%20that%20are%20changing%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLas%20Vegas%20is%20still%20attractive%20to%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Schoenberger%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20it's%20a%20place%20where%20you%20can%20go%20and%20no%20matter%20where%20you're%20from%20in%20the%20world%2C%20it%20looks%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flas-vegas-tourism-decline-recession-economy-gambling-high-prices-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755763441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a4e2b2194a2d49b8aed120%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flas-vegas-to