t%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHenry%20Montez%2C%2087%2C%20recently%20lost%20his%20job%20and%20is%20embarking%20on%20some%20upcoming%20projects.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20Meoni%20may%20be%2082%2C%20but%20he%20knows%20he%20can%20drive%20an%2018-wheeler.%20He%20just%20can't%20seem%20to%20find%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-process-ai-paper-resumes-in-person-job-interviews-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20agrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20Meoni%20worked%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-a-trucking-business-make-million-in-revenue-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etruck%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20earning%20about%20%241%2C200%20a%20week%20at%20his%20peak.%20Twenty%20years%20ago%2C%20his%20heart%20and%20neck%20started%20to%20hurt.%20Doctors%20found%20he%20had%20an%20aneurysm.%20He%20treated%20his%20condition%20with%20medications%2C%20then%20had%20a%20major%20heart%20surgery%20this%20February%20that%20put%20him%20out%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20he%20was%20ready%20to%20return%2C%20his%20job%20was%20no%20longer%20available.%20He%20sent%20applications%20to%20other%20local%20transportation%20companies%2C%20and%20still%20couldn't%20find%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20places%20don't%20want%20an%2082-year-old%20driver%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Meoni%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he's%20too%20old%20to%20apply%20for%20long-haul%20jobs%2C%20and%20the%20companies%20with%20shorter%20routes%20won't%20bite.%20A%20connection%20found%20him%20work%20as%20a%20restaurant%20valet%2C%20but%20Meoni%20turned%20it%20down%20because%20he%20couldn't%20handle%20the%20physical%20demands%20and%20weather%20exposure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeoni's%20wife%2C%2085%2C%20is%20also%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-tough-for-every-generation-layoffs-great-flattening-careers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20hunt%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20very%20concerned%20about%20their%20finances%2C%20he%20said.%20She%20ran%20a%20bar%20years%20ago%20and%20held%20a%20clerical%20job.%20He%20and%20his%20wife%20have%20about%20%2420%2C000%20left%20in%20savings.%20He%20now%20receives%20about%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%20in%20Social%20Security%2C%20which%20isn't%20enough%20to%20cover%20all%20their%20expenses%2C%20including%20roof%20repair%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20fell%20down%2C%20and%20I'm%20just%20trying%20to%20survive%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Meoni%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20dig%20out%20a%20little%20more%20money%20all%20the%20time.%20Even%20%24500%20a%20week%20more%20would%20save%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20heard%20from%20dozens%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-retire-no-jobs-older-americans-work-money-struggles-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eolder%20Americans%20navigating%20unemployment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Most%20said%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20savings%20to%20retire%20comfortably%2C%20and%20that%20hundreds%20of%20applications%20have%20yielded%20no%20work.%20Some%20opted%20to%20take%20major%20pay%20cuts%20just%20to%20have%20some%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20has%20been%20reported%20about%20what%20job%20hunting%20looks%20like%20two%20decades%20after%20retirement%20age.%20For%20the%20small%20population%20of%2080-somethings%20healthy%20enough%20to%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eapplying%20for%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20feels%20futile%2C%20particularly%20in%20more%20manual%20or%20technical%20roles.%20For%20those%20who%20do%20find%20work%2C%20it's%20often%20in%20part-time%20retail%2C%20caregiving%2C%20or%20nonprofit%20roles%20that%20pay%20slightly%20above%20minimum%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgeism%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20often%20hard%20to%20prove.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fadvocacy%2Fworkplace-age-discrimination-still-pervasive-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAARP%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202024%20found%20that%20six%20in%2010%20workers%20age%2050%20and%20older%20have%20either%20experienced%20or%20witnessed%20age%20discrimination%20at%20work.%20Over%20two%20dozen%20experts%20on%20aging%20and%20retirement%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20ageism%20is%20prevalent%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20and%20shared%20some%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAshton%20Applewhite%2C%20an%20anti-ageism%20activist%20and%20author%2C%20said%20employers%20have%20misconceptions%20about%20older%20workers'%20technical%20abilities%20or%20dedication%20to%20work.%20They're%20generally%20offered%20fewer%20training%20opportunities%2C%20but%20are%20as%20motivated%20to%20learn%20new%20technology%20as%20younger%20workers%2C%20she%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20there%20is%20little%20evidence%20that%20older%20workers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F33612506%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DConclusion%3A%2520Overall%252C%2520there%2520was%2520no%2Cwhile%2520presenteeism%2520showed%2520no%2520differences%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20economically%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20younger%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BData%20shows%20that%20if%20you%20give%20someone%20who's%20been%20on%20the%20job%20for%20a%20while%20new%20challenges%2C%20they%20are%20as%20able%20and%20interested%20in%20adapting%20as%20a%20younger%20worker%2C%26quot%3B%20Applewhite%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20some%20jobs%20are%20especially%20dangerous%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-working-into-80s-rejected-from-jobs-low-pay-finances-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworkers%20in%20their%2080s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2090s%20or%20anyone%20facing%20medical%20issues.%20One%20wrong%20step%20on%20a%20construction%20site%20could%20be%20fatal%2C%20while%20standing%20for%20five%20hours%20or%20lifting%20heavy%20objects%20could%20exacerbate%20arthritis%20or%20joint%20pain.%20Some%20companies%20may%20not%20want%20to%20take%20the%20liability%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20story%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20eight%20people%20in%20their%2080s%20navigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-find-job-months-after-layoff-scared-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunemployment%20after%20a%20layoff%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20medical%20issue%2C%20and%20nearly%20two%20dozen%20more%20reached%20out%20through%20an%20ongoing%20reader%20survey%20of%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9C80%20over%2080%E2%80%9D%20series%20draws%20on%20interviews%20with%20the%20growing%20group%20of%20Americans%20working%20past%20their%2080th%20birthdays.%20They%20discussed%20their%20careers%2C%20retirement%20planning%2C%20living%20expenses%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20life%20lessons.%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20are%2080%20and%20older%20and%20still%20work%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLScB-4a6dV6jak2g6t-CoOdxFIENDSZggxHVbvsz6ry4dGoUjg%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dsf_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Efill%20out%C2%A0this%20form%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0to%20contribute%20to%20the%20series%20and%20read%20more%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-at-80-retirement-paycheck-to-paycheck-social-security-savings-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThey're%20in%20their%2080s%2C%20still%20working%2C%20and%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-after-retirement-where-seniors-older-americans-hired-jobs-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3EWhat%20work%20looks%20like%20in%20your%2080s%20for%20half%20a%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-silent-generation-working-longer-retirement-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E81%20and%20working%20to%20survive%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F90-year-olds-still-working-retirement-jobs-financially-savvy-active-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3EMeet%20the%2090-somethings%20with%20lessons%20to%20share%20on%20life%2C%20work%2C%20and%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a7b7c2b-97b7-4d86-bdf6-ad8741425a0e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I'm%20probably%20a%20liability'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20older%20workers%20who%20can't%20find%20jobs%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they%20have%20applied%20for%20physically%20demanding%20roles%20in%20driving%2C%20construction%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20maintenance.%20Some%20of%20these%20are%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fcfoi.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20fatal%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20workers%20of%20all%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Coburn%2C%2083%2C%20said%20he%20would%20be%20living%20on%20the%20street%20if%20it%20weren't%20for%20job%20search%20and%20supportive%20services%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-quit-jobs-care-parents-careers-social-security-retirement-savings-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESenior%20Community%20Service%20Employment%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20federal%20program%20for%20which%20the%20Trump%20administration%20later%20paused%20funding.%20He%20can't%20find%20anything%20in%20his%20previous%20line%20of%20work%2C%20which%20he%20suspects%20would%20pay%20him%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoburn%20ran%20an%20appliance%20maintenance%20business%20for%2025%20years%20before%20retiring%20about%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20sent%20in%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20for%20any%20maintenance%20technician%20role%20he%20could%20find%20in%20his%20area.%20He%20applied%20to%20drive%20a%20forklift%20and%20secured%20a%20commercial%20driver's%20license%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%2083%20years%20old%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20like%20a%2040-year-old%20man%2C%26quot%3B%20Coburn%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20strong%20and%20have%20no%20health%20problems%20whatsoever.%20But%20I'm%20probably%20a%20liability%20to%20them%20because%20of%20my%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoburn%20received%20%2415.49%20an%20hour%2C%2020%20hours%20a%20week%2C%20while%20training%20and%20looking%20for%20work%20through%20the%20nonprofit%20PathStone%20since%20December.%20The%20pay%20wasn't%20sufficient%20to%20cover%20all%20his%20expenses%2C%20and%20with%20SCSEP%20cuts%2C%20he%20relies%20solely%20on%20his%20%241%2C200%20monthly%20Social%20Security%20check.%20He%20has%20lived%20in%20a%20motel%20for%20the%20last%20six%20months%2C%20which%20costs%20around%20%241%2C400%20monthly%2C%20and%20he's%20struggling%20to%20make%20car%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he's%20already%20burned%20through%20%24150%2C000%20he%20saved%20for%20retirement.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20Security%20does%20not%20pay%20you%20enough%20money%20to%20even%20live%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Coburn.%20%26quot%3BBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20I'm%20broke.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Officer%2C%20president%20and%20CEO%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20CWI%20Works%2C%20which%20helps%20older%20Americans%20secure%20work%2C%20said%20more%20employers%20need%20to%20recognize%20the%20benefits%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-job-market-ageism-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20older%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Older%20workers%20often%20have%20deep%20experience%20in%20soft%20skills%20like%20teamwork%20and%20communication%2C%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20traits%20that%20come%20with%20wisdom%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIfeoma%20Ajunwa%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Emory%20Law%20School%2C%20found%20in%20a%20study%20that%20hiring%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresearchers-ai-bots-social-media-network-experiment-toxic-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E%20use%20practices%20that%20deter%20older%20people%20from%20applying%20%E2%80%94%20like%20job%20postings%20with%20ageist%20language%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20natives%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Benergetic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAjunwa%20said%20that%20AI%20has%20opened%20doors%20for%20some%20older%20workers%2C%20making%20remote%20work%20easier%20and%20streamlining%20tasks%20with%20AI%20assistants.%20Older%20workers%20who%20struggle%20to%20adopt%20AI%20could%20be%20left%20behind%2C%20she%20said.%20And%20some%20hiring%20sites%20have%20used%20AI%20to%20estimate%20a%20candidate's%20age%20by%20scanning%20graduation%20dates%20or%20years%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pat%20is%20carefully%20organizing%20her%20collection%20of%20pictures%20on%20the%20chimney%20shelves.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6892258a3d5881a51c1e9f84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPat%20Fagin%20Scott%2C%2085%2C%20has%20struggled%20to%20find%20work.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22323a003c-78c7-4634-8d23-35223d88e49a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'I'm%20sinking%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20sinking%20fast%20enough%20to%20drown%20yet.'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20long%20and%20varied%20career%20isn't%20a%20guarantee%20of%20being%20able%20to%20find%20work%20in%20your%2080s.%20Pat%20Fagin%20Scott%2C%2085%2C%20stopped%20putting%20her%20age%20on%20her%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20has%20applied%20to%20any%20relevant%20job%20she%20could%20find.%20It's%20proven%20fruitless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%2C%20a%20Howard%20University%20graduate%2C%20began%20her%20career%20in%20teaching%20before%20working%20as%20a%20tour%20guide%20at%20the%20United%20Nations.%20She%20held%20jobs%20in%20the%20film%20industry%2C%20worked%20at%20the%20Urban%20Institute%2C%20and%20spent%2016%20years%20at%20the%20DC%20Housing%20Authority.%20She's%20lived%20for%2047%20years%20in%20the%20same%20five-bedroom%20home%20in%20Northwest%20DC%2C%20which%20is%20now%20too%20large%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20she%20retired%20from%20the%20housing%20agency%2C%20where%20she%20was%20earning%20over%20%24150%2C000%20annually.%20She%20expected%20that%20after%20taking%20some%20time%20off%2C%20she%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetworking-important-new-job-economy-ai-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eland%20a%20new%20opportunity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20given%20her%20long%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20has%20been%20job%20hunting%20on%20and%20off%20since%20retiring.%20She's%20applied%20through%20job%20boards%20like%20LinkedIn%20and%20Indeed%2C%20and%20she's%20networked%20online.%20At%20times%2C%20she%20stopped%20applying%20altogether%20after%20receiving%20a%20string%20of%20rejections%2C%20opting%20to%20volunteer%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20an%20old%20girl%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20a%20dead%20girl%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20applied%20to%20join%20the%20Army%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20I%20found%20out%20there's%20an%20age%20ceiling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pat%20Fagin%20Scott%2C%2085%2C%20at%20her%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a4b95c194a2d49b8aeccb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPat%20Fagin%20Scott%20works%20a%20volunteer%20job%20but%20hasn't%20secured%20anything%20paid.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Neumark%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Irvine%2C%20found%20that%20companies%20often%20subtly%20dissuade%20older%20workers%20from%20applying%20to%20jobs%20or%20call%20back%20older%20workers%20less%20frequently%20than%20younger%20workers.%20When%20online%20applications%20are%20age-blind%2C%20older%20applicants%20are%20not%20under-selected%2C%20though%20the%20hiring%20rate%20plummets%20after%20an%20in-person%20interview%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScott%20said%20she's%20sharp%20and%20active%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20prove%20that%20to%20hiring%20managers.%20She%20gets%20over%20%245%2C000%20a%20month%20between%20her%20Social%20Security%20and%20government%20pension%2C%20and%20she%20recently%20took%20out%20a%20reverse%20mortgage%20to%20cover%20her%20bills.%20She%20wishes%20she%20had%20saved%20more%20so%20she%20could%20better%20weather%20her%20long%20unemployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20so%20many%20things%20going%20on%20in%20my%20life%20that%20it's%20like%20a%20boat%20that%20is%20gathering%20water.%20Every%20time%20I%20plug%20up%20a%20hole%2C%20another%20hole%20comes%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sinking%2C%20but%20I'm%20not%20sinking%20fast%20enough%20to%20drown%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20North%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20and%20organizations%20at%20New%20York%20University%2C%20said%20that%20as%20the%20workforce%20ages%2C%20tension%20between%20generations%20could%20grow%20%E2%80%94%20and%20impact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterview-question-hiring-decision-what-gives-energy-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehiring%20decisions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20older%20you%20are%2C%20the%20more%20that%20people%20see%20you%20as%20blocking%20opportunities%20that%20some%20believe%20would%20be%20better%20allocated%20to%20younger%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20North%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESharon%20Solomon%20Rose%2C%20a%20social%20gerontologist%20who%20works%20as%20a%20ProAdvisor%20at%20the%20consulting%20services%20organization%20Business%20Authority%2C%20said%20employers%20should%20foster%20intergenerational%20workplaces.%20Companies%20should%20not%20isolate%20people%20in%20their%2020s%20from%20people%20in%20their%2060s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20what's%20called%20reverse%20mentoring%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20younger%20workers%20mentoring%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e894f6d-5fb8-4b3e-8b1b-cfd69917d428%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'You%20have%20to%20roll%20with%20the%20punches'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20older%20Americans%20are%20getting%20creative%20about%20finding%20work.%20Some%20said%20they%20became%20authors%2C%20while%20several%20opened%20craft%20businesses.%20Others%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-to-bet-your-career-on-in-2025-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elaunched%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20handyman%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227299%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Henry%20Montez%20holds%20his%20camera%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a4b9aca17a8c5b40531ab9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224868%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHenry%20Montez%20worked%20for%20decades%20in%20production.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Schukar%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHenry%20Montez%2C%2087%2C%20figures%20he'll%20land%20back%20on%20his%20feet%20after%20a%20layoff%20this%20year%2C%20though%20he%20won't%20be%20applying%20for%209-to-5%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20late%201960s%20and%201970s%2C%20Montez%20worked%20in%20film