s%20for%20four%20key%20attributes%20when%20he%20hires%20for%20his%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20he%20looks%20for%20candidates%20for%20his%20vibe%20coding%20startup%20who%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Bslope%2C%20breadth%2C%20curiosity%2C%20and%20bias%20to%20build.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20Osika%20said%20candidates%20needed%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bslope%2C%20not%20just%20skill.%26quot%3B%20The%2035-year-old%20said%20that%20a%20candidate's%20%26quot%3Bslope%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20their%20ability%20to%20pick%20up%20new%20skills%20and%20navigate%20a%20learning%20curve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20care%20more%20about%20how%20fast%20someone%20learns%20and%20adapts%20than%20where%20they%20are%20today.%20If%20a%20conversation%20feels%20alive%2C%20if%20I%20walk%20away%20having%20learned%20something%20new%2C%20that's%20a%20strong%20sign%20they'll%20thrive%20in%20the%20team%20and%20push%20our%20ways%20of%20working%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Osika%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20Osika%20said%20he%20looks%20for%20%26quot%3Bgeneralists%20over%20narrow%20specialists.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20he%20would%20rather%20bring%20in%20people%20%26quot%3Bwho%20can%20do%20a%20bit%20of%20everything%E2%80%94design%2C%20code%2C%20product%20thinking%E2%80%94than%20someone%20world-class%20in%20just%20one%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRange%20matters%20when%20you're%20building%20new%20categories%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20Osika%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20see%20potential%20hires%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcase-interview-consulting-firms-first-principles-thinking-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirst%20principles%20thinking%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20His%20company%20needs%20people%20%26quot%3Bwho%20don't%20just%20copy%20playbooks%20but%20ask%20why%20things%20are%20the%20way%20they%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20curiosity%20and%20ability%20to%20reason%20from%20scratch%20is%20often%20what%20gives%20you%20an%20edge%2C%26quot%3B%20Osika%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20and%20SpaceX%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20back%20in%202012%20that%20thinking%20from%20first%20principles%20often%20results%20in%20more%20innovative%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20normal%20way%20we%20conduct%20our%20lives%20is%20we%20reason%20by%20analogy.%20We%20are%20doing%20this%20because%20it's%20like%20something%20else%20that%20was%20done%2C%20or%20it's%20like%20what%20other%20people%20are%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20told%20entrepreneur%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkevin-rose-digg-proof-moonbirds-nfts-web3-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKevin%20Rose%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20mentally%20easier%20to%20reason%20by%20analogy%20rather%20than%20from%20first%20principles.%20First%20principles%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20physics%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20world%2C%20and%20what%20that%20really%20means%20is%20you%20kind%20of%20boil%20things%20down%20to%20the%20most%20fundamental%20truths%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20Osika%20said%20he%20wants%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bbuilders%2C%20not%20talkers%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20biased%20toward%20people%20who%20show%20they%20can%20ship%2C%20iterate%2C%20and%20make%20something%20real%E2%80%94whether%20that's%20a%20product%2C%20a%20project%2C%20or%20even%20just%20a%20hack%20that%20proves%20a%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20race%20for%20AI%20talent%20has%20seen%20tech%20giants%20like%20Meta%20and%20Microsoft%20offer%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-meta-tried-poaching-o